observations.recommendation:
We recommended that the Municipal Mayor undertake the following course of actions:

a.	Require the Municipal Health Office to furnish the Municipal Accounting Office certified copies of the Property Transfer Reports of all vaccines, drugs and medicines, medical and other supplies, and medical equipment received from the DOH-DCHD;


b.	Require also the Rural Health Unit (RHU) to submit a Summary Report of the Issuance/Distribution of vaccines, drugs and medicines, medical and other supplies in CY2020 and showing the inventories at hand as of December 31, 2020;


c.	Require the General Services Office to issue of Acknowledgement Receipt of Equipment and record the equipment received by the RHU;


d.	Require the Municipal Accounting Office to record in the specific Inventories accounts the cost of inventories at hand as of December 31, 2020, if any, and record in the specific Property, plant and equipment accounts the cost and the depreciation of the equipment; and,


e.	Establish specific policy guidelines for the receipt of properties through donations or any kind of transfer without cost to ensure proper reporting, accounting and monitoring thereof.

a. Instruct the Municipal Accountant to effect the necessary adjustment on the omissions/errors to correct the reported balances of the affected accounts in the Financial Statements;

b. Prepare a reconciliation statement for the discrepancies noted in the balances of Due to other NGAs account vis-a-vis NGAs records and effect the necessary adjusting entries, if any and coordinate or make representation to NGAs Accountant to settle the variance.;

c. Observe the additional information required by PPSAS that is not shown on the face of the financial statements but relevant to an understanding.

d. Integrate in the financial reports the qualitative characteristics such as reliability and comparability, in order to be useful to wide range of decision makers;

e. Provide only relevant but sufficient information, may it be narrative and descriptive and/or corroborating schedules in the Notes to the Financial Statements; and



f. Ensure that the submitted reports are free from substantial inconsistencies that undermines reliability of information.

We recommended the following:

a. take immediate action for the recovery of the total amount of P398,797.39 representing un-recouped mobilization fee/advances of contractors;

b. comply with the requirements for blacklisting of these 2 contractors and report it immediately to PHILGEPs in order that they could no longer participate in all government future biddings nationwide.

1.	Ensure that projects to be charged to the 20% DF should have the nature of investment or capital expenditures that would improve the socio-economic condition and environmental management in the delivery of services for the betterment of the constituents;

2.	Properly appropriate in the General Fund proper expenses for the repairs/rehabilitation   of classrooms and the upgrading of Day Care Centers and exclude the above project’s expenses in the 20% DF.

3.	Exercise fiscal responsibility and be prudent in the utilization of the 20% Development Fund provided by the Local Government Code and Joint Memorandum Circular No. 2011-01.
